ZH: 请务必理睬我的建议。
EN: Please make sure to consider my suggestion.

ZH: 我希望你能理睬我的忠告。
EN: I hope you can take heed of my advice.

ZH: 别不理睬你的父母的话。
EN: Don't ignore what your parents say.

ZH: 他似乎不理睬我的存在。
EN: He seems to be oblivious to my existence.

ZH: 我不想再被他理睬了。
EN: I don't want to be acknowledged by him anymore.

ZH: 请你理睬一下我遭遇的困难。
EN: Please take notice of the difficulties I've encountered.

ZH: 你应该理睬她的要求。
EN: You should pay attention to her requests.

ZH: 他从不理睬别人的意见。
EN: He never pays attention to others' opinions.

ZH: 我的忠告就等于白费，他完全不理睬。
EN: My advice is just in vain, he completely disregards it.

ZH: 她总是根据自己的想法行动，不理睬别人的意见。
EN: She always acts according to her own ideas, ignoring others' opinions.

